Apache Sling Content Editor 

The Apache Sling Content Editor allows to edit Apache Sling content based on the Sling API. 

++ Deploy Binaries ++
o Install Apache Sling (see http://sling.apache.org/site/getting-and-building-sling.html)
o Navigate to the OSGi Repository page of the management console within your running Sling instance (/system/console/obr)
o If the OSGi Repository page is not there, install `http://search.maven.org/#artifactdetails|org.apache.felix|org.apache.felix.webconsole.plugins.obr|1.0.2|bundle` at `system/console/bundles` to make it available.
o Add the OSGi repository URL (http://www.jcrbrowser.org/sling/obr/repository.xml). 
o Search for the "Apache Sling Content Editor" resource and navigate to the latest version.
o Click "Deploy and Start".
o At /system/console/bundles you will see that the Content Editor bundle is active.
o Open "/.contenteditor.html" at your server to see the web application.

++ Build the Sling Content Editor ++
o Deploy the binaries as described above. 
o Download and install Git from http://www.git-scm.com/download
o Call 'git clone git://github.com/sandroboehme/jcrbrowser.git' in a shell. It will create the jcrbrowser subfolder containing the source. 
o Change to the jcrbrowser subdirectory and call 'mvn clean install' there to install the sources into the running Sling instance.

